---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ModuleCompleteButton from '../../components/ModuleCompleteButton.astro';
import tarotDeck from '../../data/tarot-deck.json';

const majorArcana = tarotDeck.filter(c => c.arcana === 'major');
---
<BaseLayout title="Module 1: The Fool's Leap — The Fearless Tarot" description="Begin your tarot journey with an open heart. Learn the basics of the tarot deck, card anatomy, and establish your personal practice.">
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <p class="font-accent text-violet text-sm uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">✦ Module 1 ✦</p>
      <div class="text-6xl mb-4">🌟</div>
      <h1 class="font-heading text-5xl sm:text-6xl text-moonlight mb-3"
          style="text-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(123,104,238,0.6);">
        The Fool's Leap
      </h1>
      <p class="font-accent text-teal text-lg">Introduction & Foundations</p>
      <div class="mt-4 h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-violet/40 to-transparent"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- Description -->
    <div class="prose-tarot mb-10">
      <p class="text-silver text-lg leading-relaxed text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Begin your tarot journey with an open heart and curious mind. The Fool steps off the cliff not in ignorance,
        but in <em class="text-teal">radical trust</em>. That is where we begin — with beginner's mind, infinite possibility,
        and the courage to not know.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Objectives -->
    <section class="mb-10 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-violet/30 bg-violet/5">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl text-moonlight mb-4">✦ Learning Objectives</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2">
        {[
          "Understand the structure of a tarot deck (78 cards, Major + Minor Arcana)",
          "Learn card anatomy: imagery, symbolism, numerology, and suit correspondences",
          "Establish your personal tarot practice — your space, your rituals, your intentions",
          "Complete your first intuitive card pull without referencing any guidebook"
        ].map(obj => (
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-silver text-sm">
            <span class="text-teal mt-0.5">✦</span>
            {obj}
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Lesson Content -->
    <section class="space-y-8 mb-12">
      <div>
        <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl text-moonlight mb-4">What Is Tarot?</h2>
        <p class="text-silver/80 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Tarot is not a crystal ball. It is not a device for predicting a fixed future. Tarot is a
          <strong class="text-teal">mirror</strong> — a sophisticated system of symbolism that reflects back the patterns,
          stories, and truths already living within you.
        </p>
        <p class="text-silver/80 leading-relaxed">
          A tarot deck contains 78 cards, divided into the <strong class="text-violet">Major Arcana</strong> (22 cards representing
          universal life themes and archetypal forces) and the <strong class="text-violet">Minor Arcana</strong> (56 cards
          representing the everyday situations and experiences of human life across four suits).
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl text-moonlight mb-4">The Structure of the Deck</h2>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-violet/30 bg-violet/5">
            <h3 class="font-accent text-violet text-sm uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Major Arcana (22 cards)</h3>
            <p class="text-silver/70 text-sm">The big life lessons and spiritual themes. Numbered 0 (The Fool) through 21 (The World), they map the Fool's Journey — the soul's path through life.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-teal/30 bg-teal/5">
            <h3 class="font-accent text-teal text-sm uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Minor Arcana (56 cards)</h3>
            <p class="text-silver/70 text-sm">The everyday experiences of life across four suits: Wands (fire/passion), Cups (water/emotion), Swords (air/thought), and Pentacles (earth/matter).</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl text-moonlight mb-4">Card Anatomy</h2>
        <p class="text-silver/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Every tarot card is a world unto itself. When you approach a card, observe: the <strong class="text-teal">imagery and symbols</strong>,
          the <strong class="text-teal">colors and their emotional tone</strong>, the <strong class="text-teal">number</strong> and its numerological significance,
          the <strong class="text-teal">figures</strong> and their posture, expression, and direction of gaze,
          and the <strong class="text-teal">background</strong> — sky, landscape, architecture.
        </p>
        <p class="text-silver/80 leading-relaxed">
          Your <em>first</em> impression of a card — before you look up a single meaning — is data. Trust it.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl text-moonlight mb-4">Establishing Your Practice</h2>
        <p class="text-silver/80 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          A tarot practice is personal. There is no "right" way to do it. But here are the foundations of a meaningful practice:
        </p>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          {[
            { icon: "🕯️", title: "Create a Sacred Space", desc: "Light a candle, clear a small area, arrange items that feel meaningful. Signal to yourself that this is special time." },
            { icon: "🌙", title: "Set an Intention", desc: "Before you pull any card, ask a question or set an intention. 'What do I need to know today?' is always a good place to start." },
            { icon: "🤲", title: "Shuffle Intentionally", desc: "Shuffle while holding your question. Some shuffle seven times, some shuffle until it 'feels right'. Trust your instincts." },
            { icon: "📓", title: "Journal Your Readings", desc: "Keep a tarot journal. Date your pulls, note the card, and record your intuitive response before looking at any reference material." },
          ].map(item => (
            <div class="flex gap-3 p-3 rounded-xl border border-charcoal/40 bg-charcoal/10">
              <span class="text-2xl">{item.icon}</span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-accent text-silver text-sm mb-0.5">{item.title}</p>
                <p class="text-silver/60 text-xs">{item.desc}</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Activity: Fearless First Pull -->
    <section class="mb-10 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-hotpink/30 bg-hotpink/5">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl text-hotpink mb-2">🎯 Activity: Fearless First Pull</h2>
      <p class="text-silver/80 text-sm mb-4">
        Go to the <a href="/card-of-the-day" class="text-teal hover:underline">Card of the Day</a> page and pull a card.
        Before reading any description, write in your journal:
      </p>
      <ol class="space-y-1 list-decimal list-inside text-silver/70 text-sm">
        <li>What is your first feeling or impression?</li>
        <li>What symbols catch your eye?</li>
        <li>What story does the image tell you?</li>
        <li>How does this card relate to your current life?</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="text-silver/60 text-xs mt-3 italic">Then — and only then — read the card's meaning and reflection prompt.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Worksheet -->
    <section class="mb-10 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-charcoal/40 bg-charcoal/10">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl text-moonlight mb-3">📓 Worksheet: My Tarot Origin Story</h2>
      <p class="text-silver/70 text-sm mb-4">Head to the <a href="/worksheets" class="text-teal hover:underline">Worksheets page</a> to find your Module 1 worksheet. Reflect on:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-1 text-silver/70 text-sm">
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-violet">✦</span> What drew you to tarot?</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-violet">✦</span> What do you hope to learn?</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-violet">✦</span> What fears or doubts do you carry into this journey?</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Discussion -->
    <section class="mb-10 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-teal/20 bg-teal/5">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl text-teal mb-4">💬 Discussion Prompts</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-3">
        {[
          "What drew you to tarot? What do you hope to learn?",
          "How do you feel about intuition as a tool for insight?",
          "What is your relationship with symbolism and imagery?"
        ].map(q => (
          <li class="flex gap-2 text-silver/80 text-sm italic">
            <span class="text-teal not-italic">Q:</span>
            {q}
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Navigation -->
    <div class="flex justify-between items-center mt-12 pt-6 border-t border-charcoal/30">
      <span class="text-silver/30 font-accent text-sm">← Previous Module</span>
      <a href="/modules/2-major-arcana" class="font-accent text-violet hover:text-teal transition-colors text-sm">
        Module 2: The Major Arcana →
      </a>
    </div>

    <!-- Complete Button -->
    <div class="text-center">
      <ModuleCompleteButton moduleId={1} />
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
